HEADWORD: Galatea
<hw>Gal`a*te"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[After
<ets>Galatea</ets>, a British man-of-war, the material being used for
children's sailor suits.]</ety> <def>A kind of striped cotton fabric,
usually of superior quality and striped with blue or red on
white.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

